lead_paragraph: The Jets signed the free-agent running back Musa Smith. Smith played the last five seasons for Baltimore, where he set career highs last year with 264 yards rushing and 27 catches for 192 yards. A former third-round pick out of Georgia, Smith adds depth behind Thomas Jones, Leon Washington and Jesse Chatman.
